## Unit 3 Day 1-2: Social Responsibility in Web Use 

First, let's explore the first lesson in the curriculum. To begin, find your ECS Version 5 curriculum and open to page 103-104.

<a href="http://code.org/ecs#page=103" target="_blank">Access a Digital Copy of the Lesson >></a>


#### Key Concepts

1. Lead discussion about online security, experiences with social networking sites, blogs, email, online chatting

1. Students set up a blog and create a few blog entries

#### Common Difficulties

This lesson references a PBS Frontline special on teens and the internet.  There are some adult themes and you should view the video before showing it to your classroom to determine whatâ€™s best for your students and classroom environment.  You will want to to preview it to determine if you want to show it in class.  It might be worth finding a similar video clip.  Make sure to share alternative video ideas on the U3 Day 1-2 Resource Forum if you find alternative videos. 

